# Basic Syntax

```java
enum EnumName {
    CONSTANT1,
    CONSTANT2,
    CONSTANT3
}
```

---

# Enum Naming Convention

-> Enum name follows PascalCase.

Example:

```java
Day
Color
Direction
```

-> Enum constants are usually written in UPPER_CASE.

Example:

```java
MONDAY
RED
NORTH
```

---

# Enum Example

```java
enum Day {
    MONDAY,
    TUESDAY,
    WEDNESDAY,
    THURSDAY,
    FRIDAY,
    SATURDAY,
    SUNDAY
}
```

---

# Using Enum

```java
public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Day today = Day.MONDAY;

        System.out.println(today);
    }
}
```

Output:

```text
MONDAY
```

---

# Enum with Switch Case

```java
enum Day {
    MONDAY,
    TUESDAY,
    WEDNESDAY
}

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Day today = Day.MONDAY;

        switch (today) {

            case MONDAY:
                System.out.println("Start of week");
                break;

            case TUESDAY:
                System.out.println("Working day");
                break;

            case WEDNESDAY:
                System.out.println("Mid week");
                break;
        }
    }
}
```

---

# Enum is Type-Safe

```java
Day today = Day.MONDAY;
```

-> Only Day constants are allowed.

This is invalid:

```java
Day today = 5;
```

Compilation Error occurs.

---

# Enum Can Have Methods

Example:

```java
enum Direction {

    NORTH,
    SOUTH,
    EAST,
    WEST;

    public void show() {
        System.out.println("Direction Method");
    }
}
```

Using:

```java
Direction.NORTH.show();
```

---

# Enum Can Have Constructors

Example:

```java
enum Laptop {

    MACBOOK(200000),
    THINKPAD(120000),
    DELL(90000);

    private int price;

    Laptop(int price) {
        this.price = price;
    }

    public int getPrice() {
        return price;
    }
}
```

Usage:

```java
System.out.println(Laptop.MACBOOK.getPrice());
```

Output:

```text
200000
```

---

# Important Rule About Enum Constructor

-> Enum constructors are always private internally.

-> We cannot create enum objects manually using new.

Invalid:

```java
Laptop l = new Laptop();
```

Compilation Error.

---

# Enum with Fields and Methods

```java
enum Status {

    SUCCESS(200),
    ERROR(500),
    NOT_FOUND(404);

    private int code;

    Status(int code) {
        this.code = code;
    }

    public int getCode() {
        return code;
    }
}
```

Usage:

```java
System.out.println(Status.SUCCESS.getCode());
```

---

# values() Method

-> values() returns all enum constants as an array.

Example:

```java
for (Day d : Day.values()) {
    System.out.println(d);
}
```

Output:

```text
MONDAY
TUESDAY
WEDNESDAY
```

---

# ordinal() Method

-> ordinal() returns the position of enum constant.

Example:

```java
System.out.println(Day.MONDAY.ordinal());
```

Output:

```text
0
```

---

# valueOf() Method

-> Converts String into Enum constant.

Example:

```java
Day d = Day.valueOf("MONDAY");

System.out.println(d);
```

Output:

```text
MONDAY
```

