# Common Interview Questions

## 1. What is enum in Java?

-> enum is a special data type used to represent a fixed set of constants.

## 2. Is enum a class?

-> Yes.

-> Java internally treats enum as a special class extending java.lang.Enum.

## 3. Can enum have methods?

-> Yes.

## 4. Can enum have constructors?

-> Yes.

-> But constructors are private internally.

## 5. Can we create enum object using new?

-> No.

## 6. Can enum implement interfaces?

-> Yes.

## 7. Why is enum Singleton considered best?

-> Thread-safe
-> Serialization-safe
-> Reflection-safe
-> Simple implementation

